Chester Makana, News24 Correspondent SA police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane - Police in Limpopo have launched a manhunt for a trio crime syndicate who have evaded arrest since they were cornered by the police at Jane Furse near Lebowakgomo on Wednesday.Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said police were responding to a tip-off from members of the community about a trio crime syndicate who are terrorising members of the community in the area. &nbsp; Ngoepe said the syndicate is linked to two motor vehicles which were reported stolen at Sekhukhune and Pretoria. &nbsp; He said keys of different motor vehicles, an appointment certificate of a police officer, two RSA ID cards, bank cards belonging to different people, fraudulent vehicle documents, four laptops, a tablet, fraudulent documents for various vehicles, a bank card producing machine, bank statements, police dockets and a bank card swiping device were recovered during the operation. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.